We should like to call you at your
convenience any time after noon, local time or meet you if you happen to be in
the office in Red Hook. Our head of operations, our CFO and our owner are all
here and are at your personal disposal. To respond to your note specifically:






 With
     the granting of the CZM permit described below we can begin work in
     January; that would start with mobilization on the island, i.e. moving
     equipment, setting up trailers, creating lay down areas, making
     adjustments to roads in order facilitate deliveries and then moving to
     preliminary site and utility work which needs to be done in advance of the
     work at the actual site of the office structure. 
 The
     budget for the office is attached; it was completed and delivered in early
     November, but I did not spend any time going over it with you personally
     which probably should have occurred.  
 Without
     a construction phase contract in place it would premature to engage
     subcontractors or complete a buy out; nevertheless we have already taken
     the following steps to make sure that we are on track: 

  We
      have submitted the Master Plan and the Office drawings to EME for
      preliminary pricing and budgeting without committing to hiring them
      because the construction contract we have been discussing would
      contemplate competitive negotiations among the limited candidates for
      this work in the Territory; EME is the electrician of choice for all of
      the major resort work here; 
  We
      have started the same process with W. R. Nash for the mechanical work; 
  We
      have had the master plan and r/o improvements reviewed by Seven Seas and
      have received suggestions as to how the r/o and utilities would could be
      performed including anticipated budgeting information: Seven Seas is a
      local designer and supplier of r/o and wastewater facilities at numerous
      locations here and in the Caribbean; 
  We
      have given plans and engaged in negotiations with Grade All to perform
      site and utility work; this is a local company which has successfully
      performed all of our site work activities on our major projects here;
      they can mobilize in January, subject to your approval. 

 We
     have gone over the construction contract for this project in detail and I
     shall, with your permission, forward it to Darren immediately for his
     review and disposition. 
 We
     wish to have the privilege of working for you; we should like to introduce
     personnel to you immediately in order to create a clear set of
     expectations for both sides as to the delivery of services to you.  





Again you have my apologies for any
disruptions which may have been occurring due to my personal health issues. I
will call Red Hook to contact you about a personal meeting or a conference call
as you requested when we spoke on Saturday. 














From: J. Epstein
[mailto:jeeproject@yahoo.com] 

Sent: Saturday, December 16, 2006
2:07 PM

To: John
 Amerling

Subject: Re:












Please provide me with
the details of what exactly has been ordered for the construction date of jan 6
as promised on numerous occasions.. Have we determined subcontractors ,?for hte
job, and please provide the details of the office budget, that you confirmed
today has been agreed.




----- Original Message
----

From: John Amerling 
<jamerling@rrcaribbean.com>

To: J. Epstein <jeeproject@yahoo.com>

Cc: Darren Indyke 
<dkiesq@aol.com>

Sent: Friday, December 15, 2006 2:00:07 PM

Subject: 




I am pleased to tell you that Ms. Petersen just called me to
say that the balance of the CZM modification permit had been approved. This
covers the indoor pool expansion, the locker room and phase I of the infrastructure.
As indicated in the earlier message today we are moving forward on the building
permits for these buildings. The locker room requires engineering expenditures.
I am sending a proposal to Darren for initial review Asap. The building permit
process is underway. There was a pause in the activity because we wanted to
investigate concrete. The beams had to be designed as spliced to deal with
transportation issues. There are some details and approvals which Molyneux
needs from you.





CZM review of the library application is underway. I will
revisit that process with Ms. Petersen to get a better handle on when that
review can be concluded.  



















